    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-25T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-25T13:00:00-05:00" n="474"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d474">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.73/13: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract<note n="65" xml:id="d474fn65">Printed in full
                            on <ref target="#pg_466">p. 466</ref>.</note>]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-25T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 25, 1919, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7126. Your 6674 [<hi rend="italic">6774</hi>].<note n="66" xml:id="d474fn66">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_515">p. 515</ref>.</note>
                    …</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <p>The application for concession by the Societe Coloniale has been fully dealt with
                    by Department in note to French Chargé and summary cabled to you in Department’s
                        7043.<note n="67" xml:id="d474fn67">See footnote 60, <ref target="#pg_517"
                            >p. 517</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The Department reserves for later discussion the question of the landing of the
                    German cable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
